properties.name: <new field>
properties.text:
You are viewing the "First Card" of tutorial.

Press Right Arrow to continue!

properties.name: <new field>
properties.text:
Nice!
Pressing Right/Left arrow moves card back and forth.

You can also move to card from "Go" menu on the menubar.

Imagine card layout as below.

If you are all set, try going to next card from "Go" menu  and select "Next" menu item.

properties.name: <new field>
properties.text:
You can draw pictures using Tools.
Try clicking pencil tool on "Tools" palette and draw something
on the card! I've drawn some artwork to this card in advance.

Double click pencil tool to customize color and size.
Try other tools also!

When you are done, go to next card.

properties.name: <new field>
properties.text:
You can also locate buttons and text fields on the card!

And you are now reading "text field" object.

Try click "Objects" menu and select "New Field"
or "New Button" to locate new objects.

Then double click them and play with properties such as
style and color, drag them to move within the card.

properties.name: <new field>
properties.text:
Now let's play with buttons!

You are getting into the meat of WebCard.
You can write script to buttons and run it.

Try double-clicking "Go Next Card" button and
hit "Script" button in dialog. See the script?!

Now click "Browse" icon in Tools palette at the left,
and click "Go Next Card" to see what happens.

properties.name: Go Next Card
properties.script:
on mouseUp
	go to next card
end mouseUp

properties.name: <new field>
properties.text:
Nice click!

Now you are getting to understand the concept of "Mode".
You were in "Edit" mode when first opend this Basic Tutorial,
and by clicking "Browse" icon in Tools, you are now in "Browse"
mode, where scripts are going to take effect.

That's why you've came to this card by clicking the button.
If you are in "Edit" mode, clicking button won't fire the script, try!

For script reference see "Documents" tab on the top bar.

properties.name: Go Prev
properties.script:
on mouseUp
	go prev
end mouseUp

properties.name: Go Next
properties.script:
on mouseUp
	go next
end mouseUp
